    </div>
    <p>{{ founders.introduction }}</p>
    <p>Kappa Alpha Psi was founded at Indiana University in Bloomington, Indiana, at a time when African-American students faced tremendous adversity and isolation on predominantly white campuses. The ten founders—known as the "Revered Founders"—created the organization to unite men of culture, patriotism, and honor in a bond of fraternity.</p>
